\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {S14}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Where QCTS reduces ECE: per-degradation (ITB-LQ) and per-quality-bin (full ITB) breakdown.} The temperature lift concentrates on blur and colour-shift extremes (Panel a, top two rows) and on the lowest-quality 20\% of the pool (Panel b, top row), with diminishing returns on cleaner inputs. Negative reduction on low-contrast probes (Panel a, last row) is informative: contrast inflation \emph  {spreads} logits, so a quality-conditioned soften\-ing reduces the wrong dimension --- the failure mode QCTS does \emph  {not} repair. All values from $n_{\text  {ITB-LQ}}{=}300$ stratified probes ($n{=}60{-}71$ per dimension) and equi-population $\bar  {q}$ quintiles on full ITB ($n{=}564$ each).}}{13}{table.caption.20}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:perdeg}{{S14}{13}{\textbf {Where QCTS reduces ECE: per-degradation (ITB-LQ) and per-quality-bin (full ITB) breakdown.} The temperature lift concentrates on blur and colour-shift extremes (Panel a, top two rows) and on the lowest-quality 20\% of the pool (Panel b, top row), with diminishing returns on cleaner inputs. Negative reduction on low-contrast probes (Panel a, last row) is informative: contrast inflation \emph {spreads} logits, so a quality-conditioned soften\-ing reduces the wrong dimension --- the failure mode QCTS does \emph {not} repair. All values from $n_{\text {ITB-LQ}}{=}300$ stratified probes ($n{=}60{-}71$ per dimension) and equi-population $\qbar $ quintiles on full ITB ($n{=}564$ each)}{table.caption.20}{}}
